    • Enum Constant Detail

      • FETCH_VALUE

        public static final CacheChangeEvent.Operations FETCH_VALUE
        A fetch is a access to a key of the cache. The number of fetches is typically higher than the number of gets

      • GET_VALUE

        public static final CacheChangeEvent.Operations GET_VALUE
        Cache access from outside. Will result in on or more fetches. More than one fetch occur when the value is not in the cache and there is shared read lock (multiple thread read in parallel). Then an exclusive lock is acquired a the fetch is retried as some other thread could habe inserted the necessary information

      • SET_VALUE

        public static final CacheChangeEvent.Operations SET_VALUE
        Number of writes to the cache. This includes inserts, updates and refreshes (which is only an internal update).

      • REMOVE_VALUE

        public static final CacheChangeEvent.Operations REMOVE_VALUE
        Number of values which are removed from the cache. A removal might be triggered by cache usage or by shrinks due to eviction.

      • SHRINK

        public static final CacheChangeEvent.Operations SHRINK
        Called whenever the cache grows to large a a key must be removed based on the eviction strategy. Every shrink operation includes a REMOVE_VALUE operation

      • REFRESH_VALUE

        public static final CacheChangeEvent.Operations REFRESH_VALUE
        Called whenever an expired value is refreshed. Every refresh includes a UPDATE_VALUE operation

      • CLEAR

        public static final CacheChangeEvent.Operations CLEAR
        Called then the cache is cleared

      • MISSED_VALUE

        public static final CacheChangeEvent.Operations MISSED_VALUE
        Called whenever a key was not found in the cache. Every MISSED_VALUE operation was preceded by an FETCH_VALUE A miss might result in a second FETCH_VALUE or n an UPDATE_VALUE

      • KEY_FETCH_COLLISION

        public static final CacheChangeEvent.Operations KEY_FETCH_COLLISION
        Called whenever another thread create the VALUE for the current key and the thread has to wait until its fetched.

      • EXPIRED_VALUE

        public static final CacheChangeEvent.Operations EXPIRED_VALUE
        Called whenever a value is expired. May result in a REFRESH_VALUE and UPDATE_VALUE operation
